WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:03.404
You're witnessing
the power of Empire.

00:03.437 --> 00:05.906
I'm Cookie Lyon, baby.
I'm unforgettable.

00:05.939 --> 00:07.675
Catch all-new episodes
Wednesdays.

00:07.708 --> 00:09.210
And check out
our other Fox programs--

00:09.243 --> 00:12.012
Star, The Gifted,
and Lethal Weapon.

00:12.046 --> 00:14.548
That was the best idea
you've had all day.

00:14.582 --> 00:15.749
Only on Fox.

00:18.619 --> 00:20.488
-Previously on Empire...
-Lucious, what are you doing?

00:20.521 --> 00:22.256
(sighs)
It relaxes me.

00:22.290 --> 00:23.891
He only ever comes here
with Eddie.

00:23.924 --> 00:25.593
-Eddie?
-Eddie Barker.

00:25.626 --> 00:27.428
You don't know
the great super producer?

00:27.461 --> 00:28.929
He doesn't remember me, Cook.

00:28.962 --> 00:30.264
He has a traumatic brain injury.

00:30.298 --> 00:31.732
He can't remember anything.

00:31.765 --> 00:33.834
While Lucious continues
his sabbatical,

00:33.867 --> 00:35.869
we will produce and release
a new album

00:35.903 --> 00:38.706
for every year we have been
in operation.

00:38.739 --> 00:40.174
They work fast.

00:40.208 --> 00:42.176
The final edition
will be lethal.

00:42.210 --> 00:44.445
You can choose a different path
right now.

00:44.478 --> 00:47.181
-Would you come with me?
-Yes.

00:47.215 --> 00:49.350
Angelo is here as my attorney.

00:49.383 --> 00:52.453
I am suing for sole custody
of Bella.

00:54.054 --> 00:55.856
Listen, we have two days
until your hearing,

00:55.889 --> 00:58.359
so take me through this
one more time.

00:58.392 --> 01:02.596
Ms. Calhoun, Bella's mom,
was engaged to your father?

01:02.630 --> 01:04.732
-Yes.
-No. He had already broke it off

01:04.765 --> 01:05.966
with her before they hooked up.

01:05.999 --> 01:07.301
I would like to hear
Hakeem tell it.

01:07.335 --> 01:09.103
Oh, you want to hear Hakeem
tell you

01:09.137 --> 01:10.971
how he played hisself from jump?

01:11.004 --> 01:12.473
THIRSTY: Listen,
Skip is the best custody lawyer

01:12.506 --> 01:14.475
in the city-- just answer him.

01:14.508 --> 01:16.110
Go ahead, Hakeem.
Tell 'em.

01:16.144 --> 01:17.945
All right, look, me and Anika,
we hooked up as payback.

01:17.978 --> 01:20.214
But we both was mad at my father
at the time.

01:20.248 --> 01:23.151
-Right, Mom?
-Yes, boy.

01:23.184 --> 01:24.485
The second time...

01:24.518 --> 01:27.221
-Oh... so there was more
than one. -COOKIE: Oh...

01:27.255 --> 01:29.723
you think I was being sarcastic
for no reason?

01:29.757 --> 01:33.794
I was messed up in the head.
Things wasn't going good.

01:33.827 --> 01:36.230
Then I found out she was
pregnant six months later.

01:36.264 --> 01:37.798
THIRSTY: Yeah, too late
to do anything about it,

01:37.831 --> 01:39.099
if you know what I mean.

01:39.133 --> 01:40.734
Yo, Thirsty, watch how you talk
about Bella, man.

01:40.768 --> 01:42.803
-Calm down. -Relax, young Simba,
that's not what I meant.

01:42.836 --> 01:44.905
All right, and you
and Ms. Brown here

01:44.938 --> 01:47.007
have been raising the child?

01:47.040 --> 01:49.843
Yes. Well, only while
Anika was locked up.

01:49.877 --> 01:52.980
But it's not like I'm trying
to be her mother or anything.

01:53.013 --> 01:54.915
HAKEEM: And Bella's now totally
attached to Tiana.

01:54.948 --> 01:57.351
She hardly knows Anika.

01:57.385 --> 01:58.919
(phone chiming)

01:58.952 --> 02:02.456
Porsha, what?
I'm in a meeting.

02:02.490 --> 02:05.426
What?

02:05.459 --> 02:06.460
Okay.

02:06.494 --> 02:10.331
Somebody turn on TMZ.

02:10.364 --> 02:12.366
MAN (on TV): Years of
struggling and straining.

02:12.400 --> 02:13.767
*

02:13.801 --> 02:16.637
Now we come to the lowdown
on Lucious Lyon,

02:16.670 --> 02:19.039
who is getting ready to
celebrate the 20th anniversary

02:19.072 --> 02:20.674
of Empire.
According to reports,

02:20.708 --> 02:23.811
he has been suffering
from post-traumatic amnesia.

02:23.844 --> 02:26.380
CHARLES: Yeah, we're hearing
he doesn't remember his sons

02:26.414 --> 02:28.616
or even his ex-wife,
Cookie Lyon,

02:28.649 --> 02:30.451
and he's been lying about it
for months.

02:30.484 --> 02:32.386
So he has been defrauding, uh,

02:32.420 --> 02:34.555
all of the Empire shareholders?

02:34.588 --> 02:36.490
CHARLES: Uh, kind of like
a black Bernie Madoff.

02:36.524 --> 02:38.158
The guy's already lost a leg.

02:38.192 --> 02:39.993
Uh, if he's playing
with people's money,

02:40.027 --> 02:42.363
he is about to lose
something else.

02:49.837 --> 02:51.705
Morning, Detective.

02:56.444 --> 02:58.312
Oh...

02:58.346 --> 03:01.349
I did not mean
to spend the night.

03:01.382 --> 03:04.051
Yeah, it was a really big
imposition.

03:04.084 --> 03:06.053
Mm.

03:07.288 --> 03:10.558
This, we're not doing.

03:10.591 --> 03:12.426
We are not doing sleepovers.

03:12.460 --> 03:16.397
Absolutely right.
Get out.

03:16.430 --> 03:18.466
Well, since I'm here...

03:21.134 --> 03:22.636
(phone vibrates)

03:26.374 --> 03:28.208
I was just going
to hand it to you.

03:28.242 --> 03:29.577
Now you don't have to.

03:36.717 --> 03:38.419
Something about
my father's case?

03:38.452 --> 03:41.955
Now, you know I can't
talk to you about that.

03:41.989 --> 03:43.791
Well, you're doing a lot
of things that you, uh,

03:43.824 --> 03:45.459
shouldn't be doing.

03:45.493 --> 03:47.361
I guess we both just like

03:47.395 --> 03:50.298
to live on the edge,
now, don't we?

03:52.900 --> 03:55.803
And I'm not talking to you
about your father's case,

03:55.836 --> 03:59.973
unless, of course, there's
something you want to confess.

04:01.575 --> 04:03.076
Hmm.

04:14.922 --> 04:16.557
Dwight, I...

04:16.590 --> 04:19.327
I crossed a line with you.

04:19.360 --> 04:23.631
And I really need to get
a handle on my feelings.

04:23.664 --> 04:25.132
Why?

04:25.165 --> 04:28.168
Because it's... (sighs)
unprofessional.

04:28.201 --> 04:31.238
Some would say unethical.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.673
And if anybody were
to find out...

04:32.706 --> 04:35.476
Like who? Cookie?

04:35.509 --> 04:37.445
You're worried she's going
to find out about this?

04:37.478 --> 04:39.279
N-No, I'm not afraid of Cookie.

04:39.313 --> 04:41.782
(groans)
This...

04:43.317 --> 04:46.654
...it's just, um...

04:46.687 --> 04:47.921
it's my commitment,

04:47.955 --> 04:50.758
it's my responsibility.

04:50.791 --> 04:52.460
My sole purpose for being here

04:52.493 --> 04:54.428
is to help you recover
your memory.

04:54.462 --> 04:57.865
I owe that to you.
I owe it to your family.

04:57.898 --> 05:00.901
I want to remember, but...

05:05.573 --> 05:09.209
...then again,
I don't want to remember.

05:09.242 --> 05:13.213
I think the reason
I'm so conflicted

05:13.246 --> 05:15.916
is I want to help you
recover your memory...

05:18.251 --> 05:20.120
...but I want to help you
to become the man

05:20.153 --> 05:22.456
you want to be.

05:22.490 --> 05:25.793
I want to help you
to become Dwight.

05:25.826 --> 05:29.229
Is there...

05:29.262 --> 05:31.532
is there anything about Lucious

05:31.565 --> 05:35.235
you think you could embrace?

05:35.268 --> 05:38.038
His music.

05:39.840 --> 05:42.242
Lucious, we have us a problem.

05:42.275 --> 05:46.046
And I bet you that bitch Anika
leaked the damn story.

05:46.079 --> 05:48.382
Wait a minute, you paid her
$25 million.

05:48.416 --> 05:50.117
Well, that's what it got us.

05:52.052 --> 05:54.688
Then, good. Then nobody has
to pretend anymore.

05:54.722 --> 05:56.690
Lucious, yes, it is
a big problem, okay,

05:56.724 --> 05:59.593
because the board is up my ass.

05:59.627 --> 06:02.195
Okay, for months, I've been
fighting to protect

06:02.229 --> 06:04.765
the legacy you built,
but I can't do it anymore.

06:04.798 --> 06:07.367
So you're gonna have to come
with me and tell these people

06:07.401 --> 06:08.669
that this is fake news.

06:08.702 --> 06:09.670
Sorry, Claudia.

06:09.703 --> 06:11.572
No problem.

06:15.308 --> 06:17.377
*

06:23.951 --> 06:26.520
-(reporters clamoring)
-Lucious! -Mr. Lyon!

06:26.554 --> 06:30.090
Uh, I may need you to make
a statement about his condition.

06:30.123 --> 06:32.460
As long as you don't
expect me to lie.

06:32.493 --> 06:33.594
Hello.

06:33.627 --> 06:35.295
MAN:
Morning.

06:35.328 --> 06:36.897
COOKIE:
Thank you.

06:36.930 --> 06:39.032
Shareholders are bombarding us
with questions.

06:39.066 --> 06:41.034
EDNA: Investors are
threatening to sue.

06:41.068 --> 06:42.470
And if we've been defrauding
our stockholders...

06:42.503 --> 06:44.304
No one's defrauding anyone here.

06:44.337 --> 06:45.973
Can you all just give us
a chance to speak?

06:46.006 --> 06:47.508
SHINE:
I want to hear Lucious speak.

06:49.342 --> 06:52.212
Seem like he been absent.
Like he's hiding.

06:52.245 --> 06:55.148
How you feeling, L?
Been back in the studio?

06:55.182 --> 06:59.286
Moonshine.
My dear old friend.

06:59.319 --> 07:02.089
It's not about friendship now.

07:02.122 --> 07:03.957
It's about you losing
your marbles,

07:03.991 --> 07:05.759
and my 25% percent
right along with it.

07:05.793 --> 07:07.394
Hey, okay, look, you wouldn't
have a percentage

07:07.427 --> 07:08.629
if it wasn't for Lucious,

07:08.662 --> 07:10.263
so if I was you,
I'd stay in my lane.

07:10.297 --> 07:12.099
LEONARD:
We just need straight answers.

07:12.132 --> 07:16.369
Lucious, what, exactly,
is your medical condition?

07:20.841 --> 07:25.646
I'm sorry,
I don't answer to you.

07:25.679 --> 07:28.982
Nor do I answer to you or
anybody else in this room.

07:30.618 --> 07:32.853
Now, the last time I checked,

07:32.886 --> 07:36.657
Empire's stock was worth more
than it's ever been,

07:36.690 --> 07:40.193
Thanks to sale of my catalog,
thanks to the kindness

07:40.227 --> 07:43.263
of someone who wanted
to blow me up.

07:43.296 --> 07:45.866
So, I think y'all can skip me

07:45.899 --> 07:48.268
with these questions.

07:48.301 --> 07:51.271
Okay, all right,
thank you, Lucious.

07:51.304 --> 07:52.640
So, are we done here?

07:52.673 --> 07:54.942
We'd still like
a medical evaluation.

07:54.975 --> 07:57.144
Bitch, I would like a medical
evaluation of everybody

07:57.177 --> 07:59.847
on this board, but I can't
have that, can I?

07:59.880 --> 08:02.516
You know what, we are too busy
running this Empire

08:02.550 --> 08:04.518
to do this with y'all.

08:04.552 --> 08:07.387
Lucious is here to oversee
the remixes

08:07.420 --> 08:10.023
for the first 20 For 20--
we don't have time for this.

08:10.057 --> 08:11.859
REPORTER: Mr. Lyon, can you give
a quick statement...?

08:11.892 --> 08:14.361
WOMAN: What are we gonna tell
those reporters, Cookie?

08:14.394 --> 08:18.398
What if I invite the press...

08:18.431 --> 08:20.568
to follow him for 48 hours?

08:20.601 --> 08:23.370
Hmm?
The album drops right on time.

08:23.403 --> 08:26.640
Will that be enough for everyone
to calm the hell down?

08:26.674 --> 08:28.075
-I guess so.
-That could be good.

08:28.108 --> 08:29.843
SHINE:
Seems risky.

08:29.877 --> 08:32.412
-Is that good for you, Lucious?
-Damn good.

08:32.445 --> 08:34.447
Looks like we got us a deal.

08:39.920 --> 08:44.057
* I think she love me, 'cause I
got the check on me *

08:44.091 --> 08:46.594
* Wan' spend the day
and flex on me *

08:46.627 --> 08:48.195
* Put a curse and hex on me

08:48.228 --> 08:50.998
* Scratch out my name,
put the "X" on me... *

08:51.031 --> 08:53.100
Sorry I can't get coffee
with you,

08:53.133 --> 08:56.436
but the board is freaking out,
my mom's rallying the troops.

08:56.469 --> 08:58.005
So I got to get my ass
in the studio.

08:58.038 --> 09:00.107
Ah, don't worry about it.

09:00.140 --> 09:01.575
That's what I love about
your family.

09:01.609 --> 09:03.276
Dave, you can drop me
right here

09:03.310 --> 09:05.512
and then drop Warren off
to his office.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.047
WARREN: Don't worry about it.
I'll get out with you.

09:07.080 --> 09:08.048
-I'm gonna catch the subway.
-All right.

09:08.081 --> 09:09.082
All right.

09:11.885 --> 09:14.021
Jamal, what luck.

09:14.054 --> 09:16.123
Now I don't have to worry
about talking my way inside.

09:16.156 --> 09:17.357
You dropped that.
Ah, got you.

09:17.390 --> 09:19.126
That's actually a subpoena.

09:19.159 --> 09:22.529
So I guess I'll be seeing you
at, uh, Bella's custody hearing.

09:22.562 --> 09:25.298
-Call security.
-Hey, easy. Easy now.

09:25.332 --> 09:27.067
You know you don't need
any more legal problems.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.435
Look, you gave him the subpoena,
so why don't you

09:28.468 --> 09:29.436
just get the hell out of here?

09:29.469 --> 09:31.104
Okay. Who is this,

09:31.138 --> 09:32.806
your latest rent boy?

09:32.840 --> 09:36.043
'Cause he's, uh, he's taller
and dumber than I thought.

09:36.076 --> 09:38.812
Okay, take care.

09:38.846 --> 09:41.414
Oh, shoot, I almost forgot.

09:41.448 --> 09:43.116
Have you ever wondered
how the press got

09:43.150 --> 09:45.819
all those dirty little
details about your pops?

09:49.189 --> 09:52.960
Your trick looks thirsty.

09:52.993 --> 09:55.829
-Jamal...
-Just ignore what he said.

09:55.863 --> 09:59.132
He's been salty since my mom
dropped his stupid ass.

10:02.502 --> 10:04.204
Good looking out.

10:06.606 --> 10:08.809
This is so risky, Cookie.

10:08.842 --> 10:10.410
I know that Dwight's gonna
want to do this

10:10.443 --> 10:11.411
because he cares
about his family...

10:11.444 --> 10:13.013
Wait, you go by Dwight now?

10:13.046 --> 10:14.848
Never mind, child.

10:14.882 --> 10:16.249
But he hasn't even reconnected
with his musicality.

10:16.283 --> 10:17.484
I don't even know if you know

10:17.517 --> 10:19.687
your way around
a recording studio.

10:19.720 --> 10:21.755
That's why Becky is here.
She can help him.

10:21.789 --> 10:23.423
-Becky?!
-Yeah, Becky.

10:23.456 --> 10:25.125
You want me to teach
Lucious Lyon

10:25.158 --> 10:27.427
how to produce music? How?

10:27.460 --> 10:29.162
-You are being so dramatic.
-Well,

10:29.196 --> 10:31.031
you don't really have
to teach me anything, Becky.

10:31.064 --> 10:34.001
I just need you
to navigate the room.

10:34.034 --> 10:35.602
Like a Sherpa.

10:35.635 --> 10:38.338
And the studio is our mountain.

10:38.371 --> 10:40.373
And what if I'm afraid
of heights?

10:40.407 --> 10:42.042
You've spent more time with him

10:42.075 --> 10:44.211
in the studio
than anyone, Becky, okay?

10:44.244 --> 10:45.713
Just give him a few tips
about how he rolls,

10:45.746 --> 10:47.948
and let us know it's safe
to bring the press in here.

10:47.981 --> 10:49.316
-Press?
-COOKIE: Exactly. Yes.

10:49.349 --> 10:50.951
Yes! You can do, you can do.

10:50.984 --> 10:52.619
CLAUDIA:
Okay, then, I think that I need

10:52.652 --> 10:54.287
to stick close by him this time.

10:54.321 --> 10:55.522
COOKIE: Okay, look, you may not
know how to lie,

10:55.555 --> 10:57.290
but Lucious is good at it.

10:57.324 --> 11:00.828
I don't care-- long as those
reporters buy it, I'm good.

11:00.861 --> 11:03.997
So, Bella's mother,
your one-time stepmother,

11:04.031 --> 11:07.034
was charged with the murder
of your father's brother?

11:07.067 --> 11:09.336
-Half brother. okay?
-THIRSTY: Look, FYI.

11:09.369 --> 11:12.039
Anika's lawyer, Angelo Dubois,

11:12.072 --> 11:13.140
he used to kick it
with Hakeem's mom.

11:13.173 --> 11:14.708
-(chuckles)
-Pretty.

11:14.742 --> 11:16.309
I can't make this up.
Just to add

11:16.343 --> 11:18.378
a little, you know,
gasoline to the fire.

11:18.411 --> 11:19.646
Look, man, I need your word
they're not gonna try

11:19.679 --> 11:21.214
to take my baby
away from me again.

11:21.248 --> 11:22.515
Well, any more
twisted relationships

11:22.549 --> 11:23.851
between your two families?

11:23.884 --> 11:25.418
Anything you're leaving out?

11:25.452 --> 11:26.920
I need to know everything.

11:28.889 --> 11:30.590
That's it.

11:30.623 --> 11:33.260
Then you have my word.

11:34.427 --> 11:35.495
ZOE:
That's great, Bella.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.765
Y'all been granted
access behind the scenes

11:37.798 --> 11:40.167
to get a sneak peak into
the mind of a musical genius.

11:40.200 --> 11:42.002
Oh, excuse me, Cookie.

11:42.035 --> 11:44.237
Uh, these are Lucious' top ten
choices for the album cover.

11:44.271 --> 11:46.339
Uh, narrow it down to three,

11:46.373 --> 11:48.909
-and make sure you get him
to sign off on it. -Copy.

11:48.942 --> 11:51.244
Oh, and you did
have him sign off

11:51.278 --> 11:53.113
on Titan and Delphine's remix?

11:53.146 --> 11:54.547
You mean the one you d...

11:54.581 --> 11:55.682
Hey.

11:55.715 --> 11:56.750
Yes.
(chuckles)

11:56.784 --> 11:58.952
-Yes, I did.
-Okay, so...

11:58.986 --> 12:01.188
our first 20 For 20
is a compilation

12:01.221 --> 12:03.023
of Lucious's number one hits.

12:03.056 --> 12:05.592
Who's ready to see history
be remade?

12:05.625 --> 12:07.227
-Oh, yeah.
-Follow me.

12:07.260 --> 12:09.329
-(Cookie chuckles)
-(door opens)

12:11.598 --> 12:15.969
* It's so hard to believe

12:16.003 --> 12:19.106
* That you're not here with me

12:20.673 --> 12:24.444
* I really missed my chance

12:24.477 --> 12:28.949
* It's so hard to understand

12:28.982 --> 12:32.786
* But now I'm wondering,
would you *

12:32.820 --> 12:37.124
* Let me try again?

12:37.157 --> 12:39.059
Wow.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.627
-Are you okay?
-* Do you remember me?

12:40.660 --> 12:42.395
I just realized something.

12:42.429 --> 12:44.397
* Do you still think of me?

12:44.431 --> 12:47.000
It's like a door opened up. Hmm.

12:47.034 --> 12:50.137
Okay. But do you remember
what we planned?

12:50.170 --> 12:52.639
* At night

12:52.672 --> 12:56.409
* Every time you dream...

12:56.443 --> 12:58.478
Veronica, stop.
Stop, stop, stop.

12:59.813 --> 13:01.248
(Lucious chuckles)

13:01.281 --> 13:04.684
That little part right there,
that deserves...

13:04.717 --> 13:06.619
that deserves all of your power.

13:06.653 --> 13:07.855
Not just some of it.

13:07.888 --> 13:09.957
Now, I need you to imagine

13:09.990 --> 13:12.625
that if, after all these years,

13:12.659 --> 13:16.830
if everything you've
ever sacrificed,

13:16.864 --> 13:20.633
of being able to sing
in front of the world,

13:20.667 --> 13:23.270
if this moment was going to be
taken away from you,

13:23.303 --> 13:27.040
because you didn't give it
everything you've got.

13:27.074 --> 13:29.609
And I need you to sing
like you're gonna lose it

13:29.642 --> 13:31.344
at this moment.

13:31.378 --> 13:33.646
REPORTER:
Knows his stuff.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.682
-REPORTER 2: It's incredible.
-REPORTER 3: Wow.

13:35.715 --> 13:38.218
BECKY:
That's his genius.

13:38.251 --> 13:42.189
Take her back to the beginning.

13:42.222 --> 13:44.557
Take her back.

13:44.591 --> 13:47.494
* Here I sit

13:47.527 --> 13:48.996
* All alone

13:49.029 --> 13:53.967
* Wondering what went wrong

13:54.001 --> 13:56.003
* It's so hard

13:56.036 --> 13:58.638
* To believe

13:58.671 --> 14:00.908
* That you're not here

14:00.941 --> 14:03.376
* With me.

14:28.936 --> 14:30.103
Getting greedy, aren't we?

14:30.137 --> 14:32.005
PAMELA:
Not so fast, big boy.

14:32.039 --> 14:33.573
I'm here on business.

14:33.606 --> 14:35.375
Ah, what kind of business?

14:35.408 --> 14:37.410
Your boy, Shine Johnson.

14:37.444 --> 14:39.412
-He's not my boy.
-Vegas Metro's

14:39.446 --> 14:42.682
got video cam footage
of him near the garage

14:42.715 --> 14:45.285
where your father was getting
his car detailed the night of.

14:45.318 --> 14:46.519
So?

14:46.553 --> 14:47.854
My father and Shine are friends.

14:47.887 --> 14:49.522
They go way back.

14:49.556 --> 14:52.792
Our investigation says
they're more like rivals.

14:52.825 --> 14:55.963
You know, they've had
their ups and downs.

14:55.996 --> 14:57.797
I highly doubt Shine
had anything to do

14:57.830 --> 14:59.632
with my father's car bombing.

14:59.666 --> 15:02.469
Well, that's what he said
when we questioned him today.

15:02.502 --> 15:05.205
I asked you about my dad's case,
and you got all tight-lipped.

15:05.238 --> 15:08.441
Why the sudden change?

15:08.475 --> 15:11.144
-He threw shade your way, Andre.
-Shade?

15:11.178 --> 15:12.245
I'm just giving you
an opportunity

15:12.279 --> 15:13.380
to get in front of it.

15:13.413 --> 15:14.982
Get in front of it?

15:15.015 --> 15:19.419
Look, I already told Vegas Metro
everything I know.

15:19.452 --> 15:21.054
Okay.

15:21.088 --> 15:22.755
You're in front of it, then.

15:23.991 --> 15:25.425
(sighs)

15:25.458 --> 15:27.494
-I got to get back to work.
-So soon?

15:34.501 --> 15:36.503
Yeah.

15:41.108 --> 15:42.675
Hey.

15:46.313 --> 15:47.614
BECKY: Tony and Jamal
are remaking "You Won't,"

15:47.647 --> 15:49.516
which was made famous
in the '90s

15:49.549 --> 15:51.651
by Lucious and Schoolly D.

15:51.684 --> 15:54.087
Uh, interesting choice
for Jamal.

15:54.121 --> 15:56.356
Uh, Lucious, do you still
stand by those lyrics?

15:56.389 --> 15:58.325
A lot of people find them
pretty offensive.

15:58.358 --> 15:59.492
LUCIOUS:
I stand behind everything

15:59.526 --> 16:01.294
I've ever done, lady.

16:01.328 --> 16:03.630
Yeah, you know what? We're
actually still working on it.

16:03.663 --> 16:05.932
So, Dad, maybe everybody could
come back a little bit later?

16:05.965 --> 16:07.200
Good idea. Okay.

16:07.234 --> 16:08.601
BECKY:
Oh, yeah, and you know what?

16:08.635 --> 16:10.503
Shine actually needs your ear
in studio three,

16:10.537 --> 16:12.472
-so why don't we all just go...
-Uh, Cookie,

16:12.505 --> 16:14.707
-I don't, um...
-What is the pr...?

16:14.741 --> 16:17.610
Uh, no problem.
Just Shine, maybe we can wait.

16:17.644 --> 16:20.347
-LUCIOUS: It's fine.
-Seems a little tense in here.

16:20.380 --> 16:23.683
Is there any truth to the rumors
about Lucious's memory?

16:23.716 --> 16:26.453
Oh, no, no. There's no truth
about any rumors.

16:26.486 --> 16:27.954
And if that's what
y'all are snooping around for,

16:27.987 --> 16:29.222
you're in the wrong place.
You know what?

16:29.256 --> 16:31.191
-Let's go. Let's go...
-Everyone,

16:31.224 --> 16:33.460
-just follow me. -Mm-hmm, don't
be cutting your eyes at me,

16:33.493 --> 16:34.494
little Annie.

16:34.527 --> 16:36.229
Come on.

16:41.834 --> 16:44.537
As we were.

16:44.571 --> 16:46.073
Hey.

16:46.106 --> 16:47.974
Remember, you would say,

16:48.007 --> 16:49.409
"What you got for me, Shine?"

16:49.442 --> 16:52.011
-Not "Moonshine." Shine. Okay?
-(stopper squeaks)

16:54.514 --> 16:56.516
You better not play me
in front of the press

16:56.549 --> 16:57.984
like you did in the boardroom.

16:58.017 --> 16:59.686
Only thing I'm playing
is the music, Cookie.

16:59.719 --> 17:03.490
Yeah, and it'd better
be good, Shine.

17:03.523 --> 17:05.525
Welcome.

17:05.558 --> 17:08.361
-What you got for me, Shine?
-You guys ready for this?

17:08.395 --> 17:10.930
Yes, we're on a deadline.

17:10.963 --> 17:12.432
Ant, turn me up.

17:12.465 --> 17:14.467
(beat starts playing)

17:24.211 --> 17:25.912
Let's go.

17:25.945 --> 17:28.881
* Black mask, red eyes,
green case, no face *

17:28.915 --> 17:31.184
