* Don't hate the player,
hate the game *

22:19.506 --> 22:22.875
* Don't hate the player, hate
the game *

22:22.909 --> 22:26.078
* Don't hate the player,
hate the game... *

22:26.112 --> 22:28.014
LUCIOUS:
I'm starting to understand

22:28.047 --> 22:30.517
what's happening
when I hear music.

22:32.552 --> 22:36.188
Yes, I know,
I know, I know, you said that.

22:36.222 --> 22:37.890
All right, let me call you back.

22:37.924 --> 22:40.192
A prostitute just wandered in.

22:40.226 --> 22:43.329
All right.
What do you want?

22:43.362 --> 22:45.064
Just what was you trying
to do out there, Angelo?

22:45.097 --> 22:47.567
-Blow my cover in front of
Jamal? -I was just making sure

22:47.600 --> 22:49.902
you were keeping your eyes
on the prize, cuz.

22:49.936 --> 22:52.405
Well, I don't need you
to do that, cuz.

22:52.439 --> 22:54.273
You know, you were looking
really passionate

22:54.306 --> 22:57.410
for a brother who's supposed
to pretend he's in love.

22:57.444 --> 23:00.246
Well, if I'm convincing you,
then I'm doing my job.

23:00.279 --> 23:02.048
You're sprung.
I'm telling Mama

23:02.081 --> 23:03.082
and then
you're gonna kick rocks.

23:03.115 --> 23:04.584
Ain't nobody afraid of your mama

23:04.617 --> 23:05.785
but your bitch ass.

23:05.818 --> 23:07.286
You're Mama's boy.

23:07.319 --> 23:09.956
You got the whole family
messed up, anyway.

23:09.989 --> 23:11.123
And you should be
helping me help...

23:11.157 --> 23:12.425
-(knocking at door)
-Diana! It's Hakeem Lyon.

23:12.459 --> 23:14.627
-We need to talk.
-Go.

23:14.661 --> 23:16.563
-(muttering): It ain't over.
-Go.

23:19.165 --> 23:20.399
Can I help you?

23:20.433 --> 23:21.601
No. I need to talk
to your mother.

23:21.634 --> 23:22.935
Ah, she's unavailable.

23:22.969 --> 23:24.303
Uh, does this drive-by

23:24.336 --> 23:27.139
have anything to do
with your custody hearing?

23:27.173 --> 23:29.308
Look, Hakeem,
do yourself a favor.

23:29.341 --> 23:31.578
Just grant Anika full custody.

23:31.611 --> 23:32.912
To hell with you.

23:32.945 --> 23:34.380
I'm a way better parent
than Anika.

23:34.413 --> 23:37.116
All right, well,
I guess you can blame your ego

23:37.149 --> 23:41.153
when you hear, uh, little Bella
calling some other dude "Daddy."

23:41.187 --> 23:42.589
Oh.

23:42.622 --> 23:44.256
(grunts)

23:44.290 --> 23:46.559
(Angelo laughs)

23:46.593 --> 23:48.828
Okay.

23:48.861 --> 23:50.497
Did you know that judges frown

23:50.530 --> 23:53.833
upon fathers that can't
really control their temper?

23:53.866 --> 23:55.134
Yeah, so,

23:55.167 --> 23:58.137
I'll see your dumb ass in court.

24:01.841 --> 24:04.143
SHINE:
I'll be home when I get ready.

24:04.176 --> 24:05.311
(chuckles)
All right.

24:05.344 --> 24:07.013
Stop blowing up my phone, woman.

24:07.046 --> 24:08.080
All right, I love you.

24:08.114 --> 24:09.849
Don't blow up my...

24:09.882 --> 24:10.883
You talking to the cops?!

24:11.951 --> 24:13.319
You trying to get shot?

24:13.352 --> 24:14.587
I'm not going down
for what you did, Shine.

24:14.621 --> 24:15.655
-What I did?
-Yeah, what you did.

24:15.688 --> 24:16.689
What we did!

24:19.659 --> 24:21.828
You the only one running around,
talking to the cops

24:21.861 --> 24:23.763
when they hemmed your ass up
a few weeks ago.

24:23.796 --> 24:26.365
You didn't talk
to the police today?

24:26.398 --> 24:29.468
Not today. Not yesterday.
Not ever!

24:29.502 --> 24:32.438
You confusing me with somebody
who talks to the police.

24:32.471 --> 24:35.274
Now boss up.

24:35.307 --> 24:38.144
And stop running around here,
scared like a little bitch.

24:38.177 --> 24:39.846
You're right.

24:41.881 --> 24:44.551
You're not pitting me
against my family anymore.

24:44.584 --> 24:47.687
You want to tell 'em
what we did?

24:47.720 --> 24:50.156
Tell 'em.

24:50.189 --> 24:51.724
SHINE:
Yo, Andre.

24:56.896 --> 25:00.032
Yo, Keem.
Uh, according to my dude,

25:00.066 --> 25:01.300
these passports right here,

25:01.333 --> 25:02.301
they'll take care of you
and baby girl,

25:02.334 --> 25:03.502
all right, man?

25:06.072 --> 25:07.707
And we got a jet on standby?

25:07.740 --> 25:10.042
-Yeah, gassed and ready.
-This card right here,

25:10.076 --> 25:11.811
that's the number for the dude
in Cuba.

25:11.844 --> 25:12.979
Call him when you get there.

25:13.012 --> 25:14.313
He'll take care of you guys.

25:14.346 --> 25:15.682
CHICKEN:
Look, man, once you flex,

25:15.715 --> 25:18.217
they can't bring you back.
No extradition.

25:18.250 --> 25:19.986
You're gonna be good.

25:20.019 --> 25:21.688
You and Bella.

25:34.967 --> 25:37.503
There she is.

25:37.536 --> 25:38.905
What's up?

25:38.938 --> 25:40.072
"What's up?"

25:40.106 --> 25:42.842
Why you been ignoring my texts?

25:42.875 --> 25:45.778
Hmm? What's going on?

25:45.812 --> 25:47.614
I'm going to Cuba with Bella, T.

25:47.647 --> 25:50.549
Cuba? Hakeem... is this a joke?

25:50.583 --> 25:52.785
'Cause I don't have time
for this.

25:52.819 --> 25:55.087
Look, if I don't leave now,
they'll take Bella for good.

25:55.121 --> 25:56.689
I want you to come with us.

25:56.723 --> 25:58.891
-Come inside, this sounds crazy.
-No, what's crazy

25:58.925 --> 26:01.293
was letting her get away with
taking Bella in the first place.

26:01.327 --> 26:02.729
She did it before,
she'll do it again, T.

26:02.762 --> 26:04.864
She who? Anika?

26:04.897 --> 26:09.235
Look, T, I know it's a lot
to ask for,

26:09.268 --> 26:13.439
but I can't be without Bella
or you.

26:17.009 --> 26:20.379
Please.
We'll leave in the morning.

26:20.412 --> 26:21.848
(cell phone chimes)

26:23.750 --> 26:25.584
They need me back in the studio.

26:25.618 --> 26:30.122
Look, um, let me wrap this up
and I'll cover for you.

26:30.156 --> 26:32.959
And I'll meet you
at the airport.

26:34.994 --> 26:36.929
You for real?

26:36.963 --> 26:38.297
Promise.

26:38.330 --> 26:40.032
I promise.

26:44.170 --> 26:46.138
-Don't leave without me, okay?
-All right, babe.

26:46.172 --> 26:47.406
(engine starts)

26:47.439 --> 26:49.375
(car door closes)

26:53.045 --> 26:56.816
* Baby, do you remember me?

26:56.849 --> 26:58.084
* Yeah

26:58.117 --> 27:00.920
* I'll do anything

27:00.953 --> 27:02.989
* To make you

27:03.022 --> 27:06.859
* Understand

27:06.893 --> 27:08.460
* Oh, that I'll...

27:08.494 --> 27:10.930
-You good, Lu?
-Yeah.

27:10.963 --> 27:12.999
EDDIE: I remember
when you wrote this song.

27:13.032 --> 27:14.500
Was right after Cookie
went away.

27:14.533 --> 27:16.468
* Again...

27:16.502 --> 27:20.406
You built this empire to show
Cookie how much you loved her.

27:21.473 --> 27:23.609
Listen to this.

27:23.642 --> 27:25.511
* Oh...

27:25.544 --> 27:27.046
EDDIE:
Feel the love

27:27.079 --> 27:28.514
just pouring
out of every, every note.

27:28.547 --> 27:30.983
* The same...

27:31.017 --> 27:32.151
I feel it.

27:32.184 --> 27:34.854
* Do you remember me?

27:34.887 --> 27:39.191
Was that good for you, Lucious?

27:39.225 --> 27:40.226
It's so beautiful, V.

27:40.259 --> 27:42.394
I felt every single note.

27:45.031 --> 27:46.833
Hey. Why don't you take a break?

27:46.866 --> 27:48.134
Grab yourself something to eat.

27:48.167 --> 27:49.568
I got to get these fools
out of here.

27:49.601 --> 27:51.537
They've heard enough already.

27:56.208 --> 27:59.378
Okay, well, that is that.

27:59.411 --> 28:01.981
Thank you for coming.
Write something good. All right.

28:02.014 --> 28:03.182
-REPORTER: Thank you.
-I got to get back to work.

28:03.215 --> 28:04.383
REPORTER 2:
Thank you.

28:04.416 --> 28:06.485
That was good, V.
That was beautiful.

28:06.518 --> 28:08.087
-Thanks. -We're gonna do it
one more time.

28:08.120 --> 28:09.521
Just-just fall into it,
trust your power.

28:09.555 --> 28:11.257
It's all right, it's coming.
It's there.

28:11.290 --> 28:13.292
-Let's do it.
-Just relax into it. Yeah.

28:24.436 --> 28:28.074
Why is it when I hear music,
I see color?

28:28.107 --> 28:30.376
Have you ever heard
of synesthesia?

28:30.409 --> 28:34.881
I want you to listen to this
and tell me what color you see.

28:34.914 --> 28:38.417
(piano ballad playing)

28:40.619 --> 28:43.222
Key of "G."

28:43.255 --> 28:44.824
Blue.

28:52.231 --> 28:54.901
This is my song.

29:02.641 --> 29:05.978
I'm holding my music in my hand.

29:06.012 --> 29:07.746
Yes, you are.

29:27.099 --> 29:28.868
*

29:52.158 --> 29:54.226
*

29:58.064 --> 30:00.799
LUCIOUS:
I remember this feeling.

30:00.833 --> 30:03.169
CLAUDIA:
Can you describe what it is?

30:03.202 --> 30:05.504
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

30:08.174 --> 30:11.043
And what the hell
is going on in here?

30:11.077 --> 30:12.711
CLAUDIA:
He has synesthesia.

30:12.744 --> 30:14.613
I already know
about his amnesia.

30:14.646 --> 30:16.448
No, no, synesthesia.

30:16.482 --> 30:19.785
It's where he listens to music
and sees colors.

30:19.818 --> 30:21.787
His brain's been rewired.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.689
COOKIE: Yeah, but he ain't
listening to no music.

30:23.722 --> 30:25.892
CLAUDIA: No, he asked me
to turn it off.

30:25.925 --> 30:27.326
The only music
he's listening to is

30:27.359 --> 30:29.761
the music in his head right now.

30:31.931 --> 30:33.599
COOKIE:
Lucious.

30:35.267 --> 30:36.735
Lucious?

30:36.768 --> 30:39.771
No, that's not what
he's doing at all.

30:49.848 --> 30:52.384
* Truth or dare,
never tell you a lie... *

30:52.418 --> 30:53.785
(muffled):
Lucious.

30:58.124 --> 31:01.527
(muffled shouting)

31:01.560 --> 31:03.029
(muffled):
Y'all need to be quiet.

31:06.798 --> 31:08.700
Dad.

31:08.734 --> 31:10.736
COOKIE:
He don't even hear you.

31:10.769 --> 31:13.539
I know that look in his eyes.

31:13.572 --> 31:15.507
He's not listening to music.

31:15.541 --> 31:18.610
He's making music.

31:29.121 --> 31:32.124
*

31:37.063 --> 31:39.398
* 'Cause you won't
bring me down *

31:39.431 --> 31:41.934
* I won't be pulled down

31:41.968 --> 31:44.370
* You won't push me out

31:44.403 --> 31:46.905
* You won't, you won't

31:46.939 --> 31:49.308
* Your words can't kill my joy

31:49.341 --> 31:51.543
* My light won't be destroyed

31:51.577 --> 31:54.913
* My love won't be ignored

31:54.947 --> 31:57.783
* And if there's
an eye for an eye *

31:57.816 --> 32:00.086
* It'll leave both men blind

32:00.119 --> 32:02.488
* Dr. King said it clearly

32:02.521 --> 32:05.157
* I know it's hard,
but believe me *

32:05.191 --> 32:07.926
* If we let go our faith

32:07.960 --> 32:10.762
* Love will never
win the race, no *

32:10.796 --> 32:12.498
* Peace and truth
is the healing *

32:12.531 --> 32:15.701
* Shed your light
on your enemy. *

32:18.704 --> 32:20.506
-(door opens)
-Well, there he is. (laughs)

32:20.539 --> 32:22.108
-Here I am.
-How you doing?

32:22.141 --> 32:23.575
-What's up, Uncle Eddie?
-All right. Ah.

32:23.609 --> 32:25.277
-How you doing, man?
-Good.

32:25.311 --> 32:27.313
So, that was almost
a complete reverse

32:27.346 --> 32:29.115
of Lucious's arrangement, right?

32:29.148 --> 32:30.682
Yes, sir. You like it?

32:32.951 --> 32:34.420
The track's cool.

32:34.453 --> 32:37.423
The lyrics, not so much.

32:37.456 --> 32:40.926
There's a difference
between a remix and a remake.

32:40.959 --> 32:43.329
I broke that song on the radio
for your dad 20 years ago.

32:43.362 --> 32:44.963
Yeah, but Uncle Eddie,
what am I supposed to do?

32:44.997 --> 32:46.365
I'm supposed
to sing lyrics like,

32:46.398 --> 32:47.966
uh, "Won't catch me
with no fairy"

32:48.000 --> 32:50.669
or "Shoot 'em down
like a sniper"?

32:50.702 --> 32:53.772
You youngsters still take
everything so literally.

32:53.805 --> 32:57.543
Your father wrote that song in
response to a political assault

32:57.576 --> 32:59.445
on hip-hop at that time.

32:59.478 --> 33:00.946
I know. I know.

33:00.979 --> 33:02.614
Tipper Gore was snatching
rappers' wigs

33:02.648 --> 33:04.450
in a congressional hearing.
Still...

33:04.483 --> 33:07.819
And Lu responded with that song,
using his voice

33:07.853 --> 33:11.390
as a declaration
of his right to free speech.

33:11.423 --> 33:13.492
Yeah, and free speech
does not have to be hateful.

33:13.525 --> 33:15.961
So with all due respect,
I'm not buying it.

33:15.994 --> 33:18.330
(laughs softly)

33:18.364 --> 33:20.166
You were always too smart
for your own damn good.

33:20.199 --> 33:21.367
(both laugh)

33:21.400 --> 33:23.235
All right, what about this?

33:23.269 --> 33:25.204
You make that

33:25.237 --> 33:28.074
the intention behind
your singing on that song.

33:28.107 --> 33:30.976
We lay in some of the tracks
from the hearing.

33:31.009 --> 33:35.647
And we make it clear that you're
commenting on free speech.

33:35.681 --> 33:37.283
I mean, that could be dope.

33:38.750 --> 33:40.252
Yeah.

33:40.286 --> 33:41.820
All right.
Damn you, Uncle Eddie.

33:41.853 --> 33:43.255
(both laugh)

33:43.289 --> 33:45.524
-Be waiting on that.
-All right, I got you.

33:45.557 --> 33:46.858
All right.

33:46.892 --> 33:49.728
We got work to do.

33:49.761 --> 33:51.597
(chuckles)

33:51.630 --> 33:53.299
*

33:55.934 --> 33:58.003
Lucious stayed up all night

33:58.036 --> 33:59.605
so that we could complete
this album.

33:59.638 --> 34:01.207
He went home exhausted.

34:01.240 --> 34:04.343
But as promised,
I present to you:

34:04.376 --> 34:06.312
Lucious Lyon, Memory.

34:08.914 --> 34:10.349
It's incredible.

34:10.382 --> 34:12.451
JAMAL:
And with this painting

34:12.484 --> 34:16.755
as the cover art for the first
of Empire's 20 For 20 albums

34:16.788 --> 34:18.357
produced by my father,

34:18.390 --> 34:19.458
we have been
exclusively launched

34:19.491 --> 34:21.293
on Empire XStream this morning.

34:21.327 --> 34:23.061
A whole 24 hours early.

34:23.095 --> 34:24.696
And based on our early tracking,
it's already set

34:24.730 --> 34:26.098
to break several records.

34:26.132 --> 34:28.066
Without spending one dime
on promotion,

34:28.100 --> 34:29.468
thanks to the nosy media.

34:29.501 --> 34:30.769
You're welcome.

34:30.802 --> 34:31.970
Well, according
to one of the bloggers

34:32.003 --> 34:34.206
you had up in here,

34:34.240 --> 34:37.976
and I quote, "Lucious
is not right in the head."

34:38.009 --> 34:39.578
Getting tired, Shine.

34:39.611 --> 34:41.079
(knocking on table)

34:41.113 --> 34:43.815
Um...

34:43.849 --> 34:46.818
I'm gonna be honest with you.

34:46.852 --> 34:50.222
Lucious is suffering from a TBI,

34:50.256 --> 34:51.657
a traumatic brain injury.

34:51.690 --> 34:54.426
But he has made
tremendous progress.

34:54.460 --> 34:58.264
Uh... This album is proof
of that progress.

34:58.297 --> 35:01.267
And he will be back
to 100% very soon.

35:01.300 --> 35:02.834
You have my word.

35:02.868 --> 35:04.102
EDNA:
We hope so, Cookie.

35:04.136 --> 35:06.972
And we appreciate your honesty,
finally.

35:07.005 --> 35:10.842
But we must protect this company
from stockholder liability.

35:10.876 --> 35:13.279
Given everything that's
happened, it's imperative

35:13.312 --> 35:15.247
that we bring in someone
from the outside.

35:15.281 --> 35:18.184
COOKIE: I knew you bitches
were gonna say that.

35:19.685 --> 35:20.852
(scoffs)

35:23.522 --> 35:28.194
I'm sure you all know
who the great Eddie Barker is.

35:28.227 --> 35:30.095
I don't need
to run down his résumé.

35:30.128 --> 35:32.498
He's one of the most revered
executives in the history

35:32.531 --> 35:34.333
-of the music business.
-Yes.

35:34.366 --> 35:36.502
Mm-hmm. Your mouth
is dropped. Pick it up.

35:36.535 --> 35:39.505
Since you don't want me
to do this alone,

35:39.538 --> 35:42.374
you got to have a man
standing over me or beside me,

35:42.408 --> 35:44.310
how about Eddie Barker?
He's family.

35:44.343 --> 35:45.711
'Cause, see,
what you're not gonna do

35:45.744 --> 35:48.013
is bring somebody from
the outside who's not family

35:48.046 --> 35:49.381
and force them on us.

35:49.415 --> 35:50.716
LEONARD:
Are you saying Mr. Barker

35:50.749 --> 35:53.452
would come on board at Empire?

35:53.485 --> 35:56.054
Eddie?

35:56.087 --> 35:57.689
I don't think
there's a person alive

35:57.723 --> 35:59.325
who could refuse this woman.

35:59.358 --> 36:00.626
In what capacity?

36:00.659 --> 36:03.362
Special advisor to your CEO,

36:03.395 --> 36:05.831
-Cookie Lyon.
-(applause)

36:05.864 --> 36:07.999
-That makes me very happy.
-That I can get on board with.

36:08.033 --> 36:09.235
-Yes.
-Amazing.

36:11.537 --> 36:13.138
(mouthing)

36:13.171 --> 36:15.006
(piano playing)

36:15.040 --> 36:16.174
LUCIOUS:
I need yellow.

36:16.208 --> 36:17.409
-I need yellow.
-Here.

36:17.443 --> 36:19.345
Here's some yellow.

36:20.912 --> 36:22.147
LUCIOUS:
Bring this in.

36:22.180 --> 36:24.049
Give me the red.

36:24.082 --> 36:25.517
Give me drums and give me bass.

36:25.551 --> 36:27.185
Do you hear that?
Do you see that?

36:27.219 --> 36:29.555
I want the strings
to come in just like that.

36:29.588 --> 36:31.690
Make sure it's strong.

36:31.723 --> 36:33.859
Let me just swirl it around
a bit. Yellow.

36:33.892 --> 36:35.294
Yeah, it's... I'm in a room.
It's familiar, it's...

36:36.462 --> 36:37.596
Is the yellow bringing up

36:37.629 --> 36:40.632
any particular memory?

36:46.405 --> 36:47.839
-I remember...
-LUCIOUS: To the Empire.

36:47.873 --> 36:49.341
CROWD:
To the Empire!

36:49.375 --> 36:52.244
I remember this... feeling.

36:52.278 --> 36:53.445
I remember.

36:53.479 --> 36:55.981
I remember what this is.

36:59.150 --> 37:02.454
All the memories.

37:05.090 --> 37:06.792
I remember.

37:10.296 --> 37:12.298
Andre.

37:12.331 --> 37:14.533
They took her away.

37:14.566 --> 37:17.803
Do you understand
what's happening?

37:17.836 --> 37:19.305
Your synapses are reawakening

37:19.338 --> 37:22.441
because your connection
between the music

37:22.474 --> 37:24.343
and the color.
This is amazing.

37:25.444 --> 37:27.379
LUCIOUS:
I fought for them.

37:27.413 --> 37:30.449
I remember you.

37:30.482 --> 37:34.119
I remember...

37:54.139 --> 37:57.108
You're my muse.

37:59.878 --> 38:02.113
-LUCIOUS: It's you.
-COOKIE: Lucious.

38:02.147 --> 38:03.515
It's me.

38:04.550 --> 38:05.651
(laughs)

38:12.023 --> 38:14.360
I love you.

38:33.979 --> 38:35.981
*

38:51.930 --> 38:53.532
(door opens)

38:53.565 --> 38:55.367
Hakeem?

38:55.401 --> 38:57.235
-Baby, hey.
-Thanks for coming, baby.

38:57.268 --> 38:59.070
Where's Bella?

38:59.104 --> 39:01.006
She's okay. She's in
the carriage. She's asleep.

39:01.039 --> 39:02.841
-Okay.
-T, I love you.

39:02.874 --> 39:04.876
-Let's go. -Yeah,
I love you, too. And that's why

39:04.910 --> 39:06.378
-we can't go...
-COOKIE: Boy!

39:06.412 --> 39:08.146
-Where are you going?
-Mom.

39:08.179 --> 39:09.915
Don't you see what's happening?

39:09.948 --> 39:11.082
They're trying to take Bella,
and I can't let that

39:11.116 --> 39:12.551
-happen again.
-Come here. Come here.

39:12.584 --> 39:14.520
-Uh-uh.
-Mom, let go!

39:14.553 --> 39:15.821
I can't lose Bella, Mom.

39:15.854 --> 39:17.022
And I can't lose you.

39:17.055 --> 39:18.590
Look.

39:18.624 --> 39:21.326
We are Lyons.

39:21.359 --> 39:23.194
We don't run, okay?

39:23.228 --> 39:25.196
We stick together and we fight.

39:25.230 --> 39:28.567
And when we do that,
nobody can beat us.

39:28.600 --> 39:31.102
I did some things.

39:31.136 --> 39:33.104
I don't care
what you did, Hakeem.

39:33.138 --> 39:34.706
You are my son.

39:34.740 --> 39:36.875
You are my blood,
and I love you.

39:36.908 --> 39:39.445
I will ride with you
until the end of time.

39:39.478 --> 39:41.447
Don't you know that?

39:41.480 --> 39:43.048
Come here.

39:59.665 --> 40:01.667
LUCIOUS:
Good morning to you.

40:03.635 --> 40:05.070
Don't look at my scars.

40:07.673 --> 40:09.575
Why you covering up the scars?

40:09.608 --> 40:12.711
You ashamed of them?

40:12.744 --> 40:14.746
You shouldn't be.

40:16.815 --> 40:19.417
Well, they're not very pretty.

40:21.419 --> 40:23.221
Well, that's what you say.

40:23.254 --> 40:24.956
They're beautiful to me.

40:30.629 --> 40:32.430
Thank you.

40:32.464 --> 40:34.032
For really seeing me.

40:35.033 --> 40:36.234
I was so surprised

40:36.267 --> 40:39.437
when you said it before.

40:39.471 --> 40:42.340
But I love you, too.

40:42.373 --> 40:44.275
-(laughing): Really?
-I love what we're creating.

40:44.309 --> 40:47.445
I mean, this... breakthrough,

40:47.479 --> 40:49.848
the excitement of it,
I-I mean...

40:49.881 --> 40:52.518
(exhales)

40:52.551 --> 40:55.887
What do you think
about me writing a book?

40:59.891 --> 41:02.628
I think you misunderstood.

41:02.661 --> 41:05.096
I mean, I... don't mean
like I'm gonna take ownership.

41:05.130 --> 41:06.698
You're the artist.

41:06.732 --> 41:10.836
And I'm... just so happy
to be your muse.

41:17.475 --> 41:19.077
Claudia...

41:22.514 --> 41:24.583
You're not my muse.

41:27.352 --> 41:29.688
Cookie's my muse.

41:29.721 --> 41:32.390
That's what I remembered
last night in the painting.

41:32.423 --> 41:35.493
I mean, it...
it all came back to me.

41:35.527 --> 41:39.731
I don't think you can trust
all of your memories yet.

41:39.765 --> 41:42.734
I mean, we...
we were at the lion.

41:42.768 --> 41:45.837
And you said,

41:45.871 --> 41:47.472
would I come with you.

41:47.505 --> 41:49.708
Dwight, remember? You...

41:49.741 --> 41:52.010
I love Cookie.

41:53.444 --> 41:55.146
You and me. Dwight, remember?

41:55.180 --> 41:56.548
Stop calling me Dwight.

41:56.582 --> 41:58.483
My name is Lucious.

41:58.516 --> 42:00.251
No. No, there is no Lucious.

42:00.285 --> 42:01.519
Lucious is gone.

42:01.553 --> 42:02.921
-(door opens)
-It's Dwight.

42:02.954 --> 42:05.023
-No, my name is Lucious.
-(door closes)

42:05.056 --> 42:07.859
Uh, what the hell
is going on here?

42:07.893 --> 42:10.596
I think you should go
and I need to be alone with him.

42:10.629 --> 42:12.864
I think he's a little bit
confused right now.

42:12.898 --> 42:14.900
I think the only one
confused here is you.

42:14.933 --> 42:16.434
You don't give orders
in my house.

42:16.467 --> 42:17.936
Now, you did a wonderful job.

42:17.969 --> 42:19.771
I feel great.

42:19.805 --> 42:22.440
My office will send you a check.
You may leave now.

42:26.778 --> 42:29.715
Uh, well, you heard the man.

42:29.748 --> 42:31.783
(Cookie clears throat)

42:31.817 --> 42:34.519
Is there anyone you would like
for me to call for you?

42:34.552 --> 42:35.721
Hello?

42:35.754 --> 42:38.790
Webb! Juanita?

42:38.824 --> 42:39.958
Can you take Claudia

42:39.991 --> 42:41.526
up to her room
so she can pull it together?

42:41.559 --> 42:43.261
Yes, ma'am.

42:43.294 --> 42:44.630
Uh, girl, you better get.

42:44.663 --> 42:46.798
-Let's go. -Uh, Juanita,
find out where it is

42:46.832 --> 42:48.533
she needs to go,
and help her pack

42:48.566 --> 42:50.301
all her things
and get her on up out of here.

42:50.335 --> 42:52.303
Okay, Miss Cookie. Don't worry.
I'll take care of it.

42:52.337 --> 42:53.839
I know you will.

42:55.907 --> 42:56.942
I knew that bitch was crazy.

42:56.975 --> 42:57.943
I should've followed my gut.

42:57.976 --> 42:59.477
Cookie.

42:59.510 --> 43:01.412
I want to tell you something.

43:01.446 --> 43:03.148
It's gonna have to wait,
Lucious. We can't be late

43:03.181 --> 43:04.482
for Bella's court hearing.

43:04.515 --> 43:06.217
And-and you got
to clean yourself up.

43:06.251 --> 43:08.453
(chuckles) Cookie, I want
to tell you what I remembered.

43:08.486 --> 43:10.789
I know. I would love
to hear what you remembered,

43:10.822 --> 43:12.090
but it's been a long morning,

43:12.123 --> 43:14.425
and we cannot
be late for court, okay?

43:14.459 --> 43:17.629
Hurry up. Tell me in the car.

43:17.663 --> 43:18.930
I'm back.

43:21.967 --> 43:22.968
Yeah.

43:34.980 --> 43:37.482
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

44:07.045 --> 44:08.379
* Uh *

44:08.413 --> 44:09.948
I guess I used to
be a scary person.

44:09.981 --> 44:11.850
* Whoo *

44:11.883 --> 44:14.820
You hurry up and fix my man,
or we gonna have a problem.

44:14.853 --> 44:18.656
They're gonna turn me
into a monster.

44:18.690 --> 44:21.993
You and me,
Cookie and Lucious forever.

44:22.027 --> 44:26.497
He doesn't even know his name.
He treats his nurse like family
and his family like strangers.

44:26.531 --> 44:28.233
We get knocked down,
we get back up.

44:29.935 --> 44:31.336
Let the games begin.

44:31.369 --> 44:34.339
ANNOUNCER:
Empire. Wednesdays on Fox.

44:34.372 --> 44:36.908
* Say it like
You really mean it *
